quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  38,43,"And We bestowed his household to him and one more similar to it – as a mercy from Us, and as a remembrance for the people of intellect."
  38,44,"And We said, “Take a broom in your hand and strike her with it, and do not break your vow”; We indeed found him patiently enduring; what an excellent bondman! He is indeed most inclined."
  38,45,"And remember Our bondmen Ibrahim, and Ishaq, and Yaqub – the men of power and knowledge."
  38,46,"We indeed gave them distinction with a genuine affair – the remembrance of the (everlasting) abode."
  38,47,"And in Our sight, they are indeed the chosen ones, the beloved."
  38,48,"And remember Ismail and Yasa’a (Elisha) and Zul-Kifl; and they are all excellent."
  38,49,"This is an advice; and indeed for the pious is an excellent abode."
  38,50,"Everlasting Gardens – all its gates are open for them."
  38,51,"Reclining on pillows, in it they ask for fruits and drinks in plenty."
  38,52,"And with them are the pure spouses, who do not set gaze upon men except their husbands, of single age."
  38,53,"This is the promise being given to you, for the Day of Reckoning."
  38,54,"Indeed this is Our sustenance, which will never end."
  38,55,"This is for the virtuous; and indeed for the rebellious is a wretched destination."
  38,56,"Hell; which they shall enter; what an evil resting-place!"
  38,57,"This is for the criminals – so that they may taste it – boiling hot water and pus."
  38,58,"And similar other punishments in pairs."
  38,59,"“Here is another group that was with you, falling along with you”; they will answer, “Do not give them plenty of open space; they surely have to enter the fire – let them also be confined!”"
  38,60,"The followers will say, “In fact, for you! May you not get open space! It is you who brought this calamity upon us!” So what a wretched destination."
  38,61,"They say, “Our Lord! Whoever has brought this calamity upon us – double the punishment of the fire for him!”"
